Gulf Stocks: Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank, Dubai Financial Market

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-05-29T12:13:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/gulf-stocks-abu-dhabi-commercial-bank-dubai-financial-market.html
Dubai’s benchmark DFM General Index
gained 0.7 percent to 1,545.42 at the 2:00 p.m. close in the
emirate.  Abu Dhabi ’s gauge rose 0.4 percent and Kuwait’s measure
fell 0.3 percent.  The following stock rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.  Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank PJSC (ADCB)   increased the most
since April 28, climbing 2.6 percent to 2.79 dirhams. The lender
is expected to hold a board meeting on May 31 to assess bidders
for its 25 percent stake in Malaysia’s RHB Capital Bhd, the Star
reported, citing people it didn’t identify.  Al Mal Investment Co KSCC (ALMAL KK) declined 4.7 percent,
the most since April 17, to 82 fils. The Kuwaiti investment firm
said first-quarter loss widened to 4.1 million dinars ($14.9
million) from 1.4 million dinars a year earlier.  Dubai Financial Market (DFM)   rose the most since May 17,
gaining 1.7 percent to 1.22 dirhams. The stock market operator
said licensed brokers and custodians are ready to implement the
so-called delivery-versus-payment settlement system, one of the
requirements for emerging markets status at index provider MSCI
Inc.  Jabal Omar Development Co. (JOMAR)   headed for the
biggest drop since November 2008, plunging 8.3 percent to 15.4
riyals. The real-estate developer in  Saudi Arabia ’s holy city of
Mecca said shareholders approved raising its capital to 9.29
billion riyals through a rights offer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
